commit_message: The genome-analysis tools are available on git-hub (ver. 1.0.0)
In ga_reads_region tool, values are not normalized by region length by default, while normalization is applied with --norm_len option(version.0.9.4)
corrected format specifier of write_tab.c(v.0.9.3)
minor correction(v. 0.9.2)
corrected manual.
I replaced my_free function to MYFREE function(v0.9.1).
I completed manual file(v. 0.9.0)
minor revision of manual.
I wrote (incomplete) manual with sample files(ver. 0.8.4).
I made --consid_ov option to improve RPKM calculation in ga_RPKM. I also made ga_my.c file for routine function(v.0.8.3)
I made make_exon_arr function to get exon arrays(ver 0.8.2).
I add --preserve2 option for ga_overlap to preserve file2 lines if overlapping(ver. 0.8.1).
I created ga_RPKM function to calculate expression levels as RPKM(ver 0.8.0).
For ga_parse_chr_fa function in parse_chr.c, I removed strcat part to speed up for reading fasta file(ver 0.7.1).
I created ga_nuc_summit function to calculate the nucleotide composition distribution around summit(ver 0.7.0).
I created ga_nuc_region which counts the nucleotide composition as well as AT content in the specified region(ver 0.6.0).
I let ga_deltaG function consider the gradient during calculation(ver 0.5.1).
I created ga_deltaG function. This calculates the free energy difference between the duplex and single-strand states(ver 0.5.0).
Let ga_overlap function to extend the peak width with --hw option (ver. 0.4.2).
Let ga_overlap function to count the overlapped peak number from file2 with --count option. I corrected minor bugs, too(ver. 0.4.1).

I created ga_reads_region function to calculate signals around summits or regions such as genes. I let the useful add_one_val function to be global function of write_tab.c. I fixed small bug of get_path function of write_tab.c (ver0.4.0).

I created ga_reads_region function to calculate signals around summits or regions such as genes. I let the useful add_one_val function to be global function of write_tab.c. I fixed small bug of get_path function of write_tab.c (ver0.4.0).
I corrected small bug of ga_reads_summit functions.
ga_calc_dist now calculates distance between two peaks or inter-summit-distance(ver 0.3.1).

For sort_list.c file, I let them sort with prev link. For write_tab.c file, I created ga_output_append function to append output lines with correct order. Finally I made ga_calc_dist function to calculate the distance between summit1 and closest summit2(ver 0.3.0).
I created ga_reads_summit_all function to calculate and write ALL signals around summits(v0.2.3).
I corrected minor error of getting file names with sepwiggz format.
ga_reads_summit now can perform random simulation. In parse.c, the strand information of random pos is included (v.0.1.3).
Let the program skip searching the signal when it passed the win (if (j1->st >= ed) j1=NULL; break;) v0.1.2
I added ga_reads_summit to calculate the reads around summits.
ga_overlap.h was deleted.
ga_overlap ver 0.0.1.
